# 1\. Introduction

This is a Software Requirements Specification for project **Team 13** proposed for partial fulfillment of the requirements of the _Introduction to Software Engineering_ course in the School of Information Technologies and Engineering at ADA University, Baku, Azerbaijan.

A web platform that matches learners with vetted local tutors by **city**, **district**, **subject**, **availability**, **price**, and **rating**-no map required. **Problem is** Finding a quality tutor who is nearby, available at the right times, and within budget is hard. Tutors also struggle to reach students in specific districts and to manage active groups/classes

## Scope and Objectives

**Potential audience, users, and user environment**

**Target users**

- **Tutors/Instructors**: register profiles, list districts, prices, availability; run classes and manage students.
- **Learners/Parents**: search by city→district, subject, schedule, price; request/enroll and read feedback.
- **Admins**: moderation, verification, catalog management.

**User environment & context**

- Web platform with fast, district-level discovery and booking; simple tools for classes and per-student feedback.
- Client is a web SPA for search, filters, profiles, booking UI (desktop/mobile browsers).

**Important mechanics to cover in the system (MVP)**

- **District catalog** (city→district; no map).
- **Availability slots** (weekly, recurring) and **filtering by availability**.
- **Search & Filter**: city, district, subject, price range, rating, availability; sorting/pagination.
- **Booking Requests**: request → accept/decline → status updates; simple inbox.
- **Classes/Groups & Rosters**; **Per-student feedback**.
- **Ratings & Reviews** (with moderation); **Admin tools** (verification, moderation, taxonomy).

**Main objectives of the project**

- **Time-to-match:** median time from search to first booking request < **10 minutes**.
- **Tutor utilization:** average classes ≥ **70%** of capacity by Week 8 pilot.
- **Quality/Performance:** P95 search latency < **1.2 s**; additional quality metrics.

**Goals to be satisfied & major features (brief)**

- **Auth & Roles** (Tutor/Learner/Admin), **Profiles**, **District catalog**, **Availability**, **Search & Filter**, **Booking**, **Classes**, **Feedback**, **Reviews**, **Admin console** (verification & moderation).

**Data we will gather and why**

- **User** (id, role, name, email, password hash) - identity/auth.
- **TutorProfile** (city, districts, bio, qualifications, price_hourly, rating_avg/count, subjects) - search & transparency.
- **AvailabilitySlot** - matching on free times.
- **Class** & **Enrollment** - group sessions and rosters.
- **Feedback** (per-student notes) - learning continuity (private to that student).
- **BookingRequest** - transaction flow and status.

**Review** - quality signals for search.

## Definitions

Term

Definition

Learner

A user who is looking for a tutor and can search, filter, and request bookings on the platform.

Parent

A learner's guardian who may create and manage a learner account on behalf of a student.

Tutor

A user who offers tutoring services and creates a public tutor profile on the platform.

Admin

A platform administrator responsible for verification, moderation, and catalog management.

City

A major location unit used to group districts (e.g., Baku).

District

An administrative part of a city, used as the smallest location unit in the MVP.

Tutor Profile

A public profile for a tutor containing city, districts, subjects, price, qualifications, and rating.

Availability Slot

A recurring weekly time window during which a tutor is available to teach (e.g., Mon 18:00-20:00).

Booking Request

A request created by a learner to book one or more tutoring sessions with a tutor.

Class / Group

A recurring tutoring session run by a tutor for one or more learners, with a defined schedule.

Enrollment

The association between a learner and a class/group indicating that the learner is attending it.

Feedback

Tutor's per-student notes about progress or issues, visible only to that student (and guardians).

Rating

A numeric score (e.g., 1-5 stars) given by a learner to a tutor after lessons.

Review

A textual comment written by a learner about a tutor, usually combined with a rating.

Inbox

The in-system list of booking requests and status updates shown to tutors and learners.

Verification

An admin action that marks a tutor profile as verified (e.g., identity or credential check).

# Overall Description

## Project Features

TutorFind is a city & district-based tutor matching web platform that focuses on **fast, local discovery** without requiring a map interface. From the user's point of view, the main features are:

**Role-based access**

Learners/Parents create accounts, manage profiles, and search for tutors.

Tutors create and manage tutor profiles, availability, classes, and learners.

Admins moderate content, verify tutors, and manage platform taxonomies (cities, districts, subjects).

**Tutor profiles and district catalog**

Tutors specify **city and district coverage** (one city, multiple districts).

Tutors describe **subjects, hourly price, bio, qualifications**, and overall rating.

The system exposes a **predefined city → district catalog** that can be reused across tutors and searches (no map/geolocation in MVP).

**Availability and scheduling**

Tutors define **recurring weekly availability slots** (e.g., every Tuesday 16:00-18:00).

Learners can **filter tutors by availability** that overlaps with their desired schedule.

**Search & filter**

Learners search tutors by **city and district** as the primary entry point.

Learners filter by **subject, price range, rating, and availability**, with sorting and pagination.

Results show key info (name, districts, subjects, rating, price) and link to full profile pages.

**Booking requests and inbox**

Learners send **booking requests** to tutors with preferred time slots and notes.

Tutors **accept or decline** requests; both sides see **status updates** (pending, accepted, declined, cancelled) in a simple inbox view.

**Classes, groups, and rosters**

Tutors create **classes/groups** with subject, schedule, and capacity.

Tutors enroll learners from accepted bookings into classes and manage **rosters**.

**Per-student feedback**

Tutors record **private feedback notes** per student and session (e.g., progress, homework).

Feedback is visible only to the relevant learner (and parent/guardian).

**Ratings, reviews, and moderation**

Learners rate and review tutors after attending at least one class.

Reviews and ratings appear on tutor profiles as **quality signals**.

Admins can **moderate (hide/remove)** inappropriate or abusive content.

**Admin console**

Admins manage **verification flags**, subjects, districts, and possibly other catalog entities.

Admins run **basic oversight** on bookings, reviews, and platform health.

These features are expressed in customer language here and will be formalized in Section 3 as testable requirements.

## Target User Characteristics

**Learners / Students**

Age: mostly **school and university students** (approx. 12-25 years old).

Technical level: comfortable using web and mobile browsers; familiar with search, forms, and ratings.

Needs:

Find tutors **nearby** (same city/district).

Match schedules and price with their constraints.

Evaluate quality via ratings/reviews.

**Tutors / Instructors**

Typically have **subject expertise** (school/university teachers, private tutors).

Varying technical skills but expected to manage basic web forms.

Needs:

Reach learners in specific **districts**.

Manage **availability, bookings, and classes** efficiently.

Build credibility through **ratings, reviews, and verification**.

**Admins**

Technically literate users (e.g., support staff) with training on platform tools.

Needs:

Maintain data quality (districts, subjects).

Verify tutor profiles and moderate risky content.

Monitor overall usage and issues.

These user characteristics influence **UI/UX design**, which must prioritize clarity, responsiveness, and minimal steps to complete search and booking flows.

## Constraints

This section describes constraints in customer language; formal non-functional requirements appear in Section 3.2.

**Technological constraints**

The system is delivered as a **web-based Single Page Application (SPA)**.

It must work on **modern desktop and mobile browsers**.

No native mobile apps are included in the MVP.

MVP does **not** include maps or geolocation-based search-location is modeled only via **city and district**.

**Business and scope constraints**

**No integrated payment processing** in MVP. All payments are handled offline or through external channels agreed between tutor and learner.

The MVP focuses on **matching and booking**; advanced analytics and in-depth reporting are out of scope.

**Performance and reliability constraints**

Search must feel **fast**; target typical search responses under **500 ms**, and worst-case (95th percentile) under **1.2 seconds** under the expected pilot load.

The system should provide at least **99% weekly uptime** during pilot.

**Security and privacy constraints**

User passwords must be stored as **hashed values**, not plain text.

Users see only data relevant to their role; e.g., private feedback is only accessible to that learner (and guardian).

Admin functions (such as moderation and verification) are **role-restricted**.

**Accessibility constraints**

The platform aims to align with **WCAG 2.1 AA** guidelines where feasible in MVP (labels, contrast, keyboard navigation, etc.).

**Maintainability and scalability constraints**

The system must be designed with **clear module boundaries** (e.g., auth, profiles, search, booking).

Basic automated tests are required for core flows (auth, search, booking).

The system should handle at least **4,000 users**, **1,000 tutor profiles**, and **20,000 searches per month** without major degradation.

## Assumptions and Dependencies

**Assumptions**

Users (tutors and learners) have:

Reliable **internet access** and a **modern browser**.

Basic ability to fill out forms and understand ratings and filters.

District lists provided by the team or client are sufficiently accurate for matching purposes.

Tutors and learners will communicate further logistics (exact time, platform for online sessions, payment method) **outside** the system in the MVP.

There is at least one admin who maintains the **district, subject, and verification** data.

**Dependencies**

Availability of infrastructure to host the web application (e.g., university or cloud hosting).

Underlying tech stack (e.g., **React + TypeScript frontend, .NET/Spring Boot backend, PostgreSQL, Redis**) is available and supported.

Email or notification service (if used) for actions like verification, booking updates, or password resets.

Any authentication service used (internal or university SSO) if integrated in later iterations.

# Specific Requirements

## Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Functional Requirements

All functional requirements are expressed as "The system shall…" statements and are externally observable.

User Management and Authentication

FR-01: The system shall allow a visitor to register as a learner or tutor using a unique email address and password.

FR-02: The system shall allow a registered user to log in using email and password.

FR-03: The system shall allow any logged-in user to log out.

FR-04: The system shall allow a logged-in user to view and update their basic account information (name, email, password).

Tutor Profiles and District Catalog

FR-05: The system shall allow a tutor to create and edit a tutor profile containing city, one or more districts, subjects taught, hourly price, bio, and qualifications.

FR-06: The system shall maintain a predefined catalog of cities and districts that tutors and learners can select from when configuring profiles and searches.

FR-07: The system shall display key tutor profile information (city, districts, subjects, rating, hourly price) in search results and on a dedicated profile page.

Availability and Scheduling

FR-08: The system shall allow tutors to define recurring weekly availability slots by day of week, start time, and end time.

FR-09: The system shall allow tutors to update or remove previously defined availability slots.

FR-10: The system shall allow learners to filter tutors by availability overlapping with a requested time range.

Search and Filter

FR-11: The system shall allow learners to search tutors by selecting a city and district.

FR-12: The system shall allow learners to filter search results by subject, hourly price range, average rating, and availability.

FR-13: The system shall provide pagination for search results when the number of tutors exceeds the page size.

FR-14: The system shall allow learners to sort search results by relevance, price, or rating.

Booking Requests and Inbox

FR-15: The system shall allow a learner to create a booking request for a selected tutor, including preferred schedule and optional notes.

FR-16: The system shall store a booking request with an initial status of "Pending".

FR-17: The system shall allow a tutor to view a list of incoming booking requests.

FR-18: The system shall allow a tutor to accept or decline a pending booking request.

FR-19: The system shall update the booking request status to "Accepted", "Declined", or "Cancelled" as appropriate and display the updated status to both tutor and learner.

FR-20: The system shall provide an inbox-style view of booking requests and their statuses for both tutors and learners.

Classes, Groups, and Rosters

FR-21: The system shall allow tutors to create a class/group specifying subject, schedule, capacity, and associated districts or city.

FR-22: The system shall allow tutors to enroll learners from accepted booking requests into classes/groups.

FR-23: The system shall allow tutors to view and manage the roster (list of enrolled learners) for each class.

Per-Student Feedback

FR-24: The system shall allow tutors to record per-student feedback notes associated with a class session or date.

FR-25: The system shall restrict visibility of per-student feedback so that only the relevant learner (and guardian, if present) and the tutor can view it.

Ratings and Reviews

FR-26: The system shall allow a learner to submit a rating and text review for a tutor after attending at least one class with that tutor.

FR-27: The system shall display aggregated rating information (e.g., average rating and count of reviews) on tutor profiles.

FR-28: The system shall display individual text reviews on tutor profiles, ordered by recency or relevance.

Admin and Moderation

FR-29: The system shall allow admins to view a list of tutor profiles and mark them as verified or unverified.

FR-30: The system shall allow admins to view and remove reviews that violate platform rules (e.g., offensive content).

FR-31: The system shall allow admins to manage catalog data such as subjects and, if needed, city/district entries.

Notifications (In-system)

FR-32: The system shall notify a tutor when a new booking request is created for them via an entry in their inbox view.

FR-33: The system shall notify a learner when the status of their booking request changes.

## Nonfunctional Requirements

### 3.2 Non-functional Requirements

Usability

NFR-01 (Usability): The system shall provide a responsive user interface that is usable on both desktop and mobile browsers without horizontal scrolling for main flows.

NFR-02 (Usability): A new learner shall be able to perform a basic search (select city, district, subject) and view results in no more than 3 navigation steps from the home page.

NFR-03 (Usability): All interactive elements and form fields shall have descriptive labels or placeholders to support first-time users.

Performance

NFR-04 (Performance): Under expected pilot load (up to 4,000 users, 1,000 tutor profiles, 20,000 searches/month), 95% of search requests shall complete within 1.2 seconds.

NFR-05 (Performance): The system shall support at least 50 concurrent users performing search and booking actions without significant degradation (no more than 10% slower than normal response times).

Reliability and Availability

NFR-06 (Reliability): The system shall achieve at least 99% uptime measured weekly during the pilot period, excluding planned maintenance.

NFR-07 (Reliability): In case of unexpected server failure, the system shall recover to an operational state without data loss of confirmed registrations and bookings.

Security and Privacy

NFR-08 (Security): The system shall store all user passwords as salted, one-way hashes.

NFR-09 (Security): The system shall restrict access to admin functions (verification, moderation, catalog management) to authenticated users with the admin role.

NFR-10 (Privacy): The system shall ensure that per-student feedback notes are not accessible to other learners or tutors who are not involved in that specific student's classes.

Compatibility

NFR-11 (Compatibility): The web application shall support the latest stable versions of major browsers (e.g., Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari) at the time of deployment.

NFR-12 (Compatibility): The system shall require no browser plugins beyond standard HTML5, CSS, and JavaScript.

Maintainability

NFR-13 (Maintainability): Core modules (authentication, profiles, search, booking) shall have automated tests covering at least 60% of their business logic.

NFR-14 (Maintainability): The system's codebase shall be organized into clearly separated layers (e.g., presentation, business logic, data access) to support future extension.

Accessibility

NFR-15 (Accessibility): All interactive controls shall be reachable via keyboard navigation, and important content shall not rely solely on color for meaning.

NFR-16 (Accessibility): All images that convey information (if any) shall include alternative text attributes.

# Analysis Models (Use Cases)

## External Actor Descriptions

· Learner

Registers/logs in to the system, searches for tutors by city and district, filters by subject/price/rating/availability, sends booking requests, views booking statuses, and provides ratings and reviews.

· Tutor

Registers/logs in, creates and maintains tutor profile, defines availability, manages booking requests (accept/decline), creates classes/groups, manages rosters, and records per-student feedback.

· Admin

Logs in with elevated rights, reviews tutor profiles, marks tutors as verified, moderates ratings and reviews, and manages catalog data such as cities, districts, and subjects.

## Use Case Descriptions

| **No** | **User story name**                | **Description**                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| ------ | ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **1**  | User Registration                  | As a learner or tutor, I want to create an account so that I can access personalized features of TutorFind.                                                                                                   |
| **2**  | Tutor Profile Management           | As a tutor, I want to set up and update my profile (districts, subjects, price, bio) so that learners can find me.                                                                                            |
| **3**  | Availability Management            | As a tutor, I want to define my weekly availability so that learners can request bookings at suitable times.                                                                                                  |
| **4**  | Tutor Search by City & District    | As a learner, I want to search tutors in my city and district so that I can find local options and filter them by subject, price, rating, and availability.                                                   |
| **5**  | Send Booking Request               | As a learner, I want to send a booking request to a tutor so that I can schedule lessons.                                                                                                                     |
| **6**  | Rate and Review Tutor              | As a learner, I want to rate and review tutors so that other learners can benefit from my experience.                                                                                                         |
| **7**  | Manage Booking Requests            | As a tutor, I want to accept or decline booking requests so that I can control my schedule.                                                                                                                   |
| **8**  | Manage Classes and Rosters         | As a tutor, I want to create classes and manage enrolled learners so that I can organize group sessions.                                                                                                      |
| **9**  | Provide and View Feedback          | As a tutor, I want to record per-student feedback, and as a learner, I want to read it so that progress is tracked and kept private between the learner and tutor (and, if applicable, a parent or guardian). |
| **10** | Moderation and Admin verification. | As an admin, I want to verify tutor profiles and moderate reviews so that the platform is trustworthy and safe.                                                                                               |

Depending on the flow, the tutor has an active schedule, blocked days, or vacation periods that are all used by the System when learners search and request bookings.</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>

online or in-person, lesson duration, optional message, and location for in-person lessons).</strong></li><li><strong>Learner provides booking details and submits the booking request.</strong></li><li><strong>System verifies that all required booking details are provided and valid and checks that the selected time slot is still available.</strong><ul><li><strong>If information is invalid System displays an error message and returns the Learner to Step 4.</strong></li></ul></li><li><strong>System creates a new booking request with status "Pending Tutor Response".</strong></li><li><strong>System stores the booking request in the database.</strong></li><li><strong>System sends notifications to the Tutor and the Learner about the new booking request.</strong></li><li><strong>System displays confirmation to the Learner that the booking request has been successfully sent.</strong></li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Alternate Flows:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Alternate Flows:</strong></p><p><strong>Alternate Flow #1: After Step 2 in the success scenario System will display the option to Cancel the booking request process. The following steps would occur:</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Learner selects option to cancel during the booking request process.</strong></li><li><strong>System requests confirmation to cancel without sending the booking request.</strong></li><li><strong>Learner confirms intent to cancel.</strong></li><li><strong>System discards any unsent booking information.</strong></li><li><strong>System returns the Learner to the tutor's profile or previous screen.</strong></li></ol><p><strong>Alternate Flow #2: The selected time slot becomes unavailable before the booking request is saved . After Step 6 in the success scenario the following steps would occur:</strong></p><ol><li><strong>System detects that the selected time slot conflicts with an existing booking or has been removed from the tutor's availability.</strong></li><li><strong>System displays a message informing the Learner that the chosen time is no longer available.</strong></li><li><strong>System returns the Learner to the list of available time slots and requests the Learner to select a different time.</strong></li><li><strong>Learner selects a new available time slot and continues from Step 4 of the main success flow.</strong></li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Post Condition:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>A booking request record is stored in the System with status "Pending Tutor Response" (main success flow), or no booking request is created if the Learner cancels (Alternate Flow #1).</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>

### Use Case 6

<div class="joplin-table-wrapper"><table><tbody><tr><th><p><strong>Use Case Number:</strong></p></th><th><p><strong>UC-06</strong></p></th></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Use Case Name:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Rate and Review Tutor</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Actor(s):w</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Learner</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Description:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Learner shall provide rating and review information to the System upon rating a Tutor so that other learners can benefit from the Learner's experience.</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Trigger:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>External - Learner selecting the option to rate and review a Tutor in the System.</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Pre-condition(s):</strong></p></td><td><ul><li><strong>TutorFind platform is online and reachable.</strong></li><li><strong>The Learner has a registered, active account and is logged in.</strong></li><li><strong>There is at least one completed lesson/booking between this Learner and this Tutor in the System.</strong></li><li><strong>The review period for that lesson is still open according to System rules.</strong></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Scenario Flow:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Main (success) Flow:</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Learner selects option to Rate &amp; The following steps would occur:</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Learner selects option to cancel during the rating and review process.</strong></li><li><strong>System requests confirmation to cancel without saving the rating and review.</strong></li><li><strong>Learner confirms intent to cancel.</strong></li><li><strong>System discards any unsaved rating and review information.</strong></li><li><strong>System returns the Learner to the previous screen (for example, completed booking list or Tutor's profile).</strong></li></ol><p><strong>Alternate Flow #2: The Learner attempts to rate a Tutor without having any completed lesson with that Tutor in the System. After Step 1 in the success scenario the following steps would occur:</strong></p><ol><li><strong>System checks the Learner's booking history with the selected Tutor and determines that there is no completed lesson.</strong></li><li><strong>System displays a message informing the Learner that rating and review are only allowed after at least one completed lesson.</strong></li><li><strong>System does not display the rating and review input screen.</strong></li><li><strong>System returns the Learner to the Tutor's profile or previous screen.</strong></li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Post Condition:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>A valid rating and review are stored and linked to the Tutor (main success flow), or no rating/review is created if the Learner cancels or is not eligible to rate.</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>

### Use Case 8

<div class="joplin-table-wrapper"><table><tbody><tr><th><p><strong>Use Case Number:</strong></p></th><th><p><strong>UC-08</strong></p></th></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Use Case Name:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Manage Classes and Rosters</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Actor(s):w</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Tutor</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Description:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Tutor shall provide class information and manage the roster in the System upon creating and maintaining group classes so that multiple learners can attend the same lesson.</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Trigger:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>External - If Tutor cancels, no new feedback is stored; if Learner has no feedback, only an informational message is shown.</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>

### Use Case 10

Verification from the admin dashboard.</strong></li><li><strong>System displays a list of pending tutor verifications and flagged content items and requests the Admin to select an item to review.</strong></li><li><strong>Admin selects a pending tutor account from the list.</strong></li><li><strong>System displays tutor details (for example: name, subjects, education, documents) and requests the Admin to take an action.</strong></li><li><strong>Admin reviews the information and selects option to Approve Tutor.</strong></li><li><strong>System verifies that the tutor record is complete and can be activated.</strong><ul><li><strong>If the record is incomplete System displays an error message and returns the Admin to Step 4.</strong></li></ul></li><li><strong>System changes the tutor's status to Verified / Active.</strong></li><li><strong>System makes the tutor profile visible in searches and listings for learners.</strong></li><li><strong>System sends a notification to the tutor informing them that their account has been approved.</strong></li><li><strong>System returns the Admin to the list of pending items (Step 2) so the Admin may select another item to review.</strong></li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Alternate Flows:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Alternate Flows</strong></p><p><strong>Alternate Flow #1: After Step 4 in the success scenario System will display the option to Reject the tutor or Request more information. The following steps would occur:</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Admin selects option to Reject Tutor or Request More Information.</strong></li><li><strong>System requests the Admin to enter a reason or explanation.</strong></li><li><strong>Admin provides a reason and confirms the action.</strong></li><li><strong>System updates the tutor's status to Rejected or Pending Additional Information.</strong></li><li><strong>System sends a notification to the tutor explaining that the account was not approved and includes the reason or required additional information.</strong></li><li><strong>System returns the Admin to the list of pending items (Step 2 of the main success flow).</strong></li></ol><p><strong>Alternate Flow #2: Admin chooses to review flagged content instead of a tutor account. After Step 2 in the success scenario the following steps would occur:</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Admin selects a flagged review or feedback item from the list.</strong></li><li><strong>System displays the content (for example: rating, text, author, target tutor/lesson) and requests the Admin to take an action.</strong></li><li><strong>Admin selects option to Approve, Edit (e.g., hide certain words), or Remove the content.</strong></li><li><strong>If Admin selects Approve, System marks the content as approved and leaves it visible.</strong></li><li><strong>If Admin selects Edit, System requests a revised version or specific parts to be hidden, then stores the moderated version and displays that version to users.</strong></li><li><strong>If Admin selects Remove, System marks the content as Hidden/Removed so that it is no longer visible to learners or tutors.</strong></li><li><strong>If policy requires, System sends a notification to the content author informing them that their content was edited or removed.</strong></li><li><strong>System returns the Admin to the list of pending items (Step 2 of the main success flow).</strong></li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Post Condition:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>At the end of this use case, the System has updated the status of the reviewed tutor accounts and content items so that only verified tutors are visible to learners and any inappropriate or non-approved content has been edited, hidden, or removed in accordance with the Admin's decisions.</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>

# Overview

This is a project proposal for partial fulfillment of the requirements of the _Introduction to Software Engineering_ course in the School of Information Technologies and Engineering at ADA University, Baku, Azerbaijan.

A web platform that matches learners with vetted local tutors by **city**, **district**, **subject**, **availability**, **price**, and **rating**-no map required. **Problem is** Finding a quality tutor who is nearby, available at the right times, and within budget is hard. Tutors also struggle to reach students in specific districts and to manage active groups/classes

# Project Description

## Scope and Objectives

**Potential audience, users, and user environment**

**Target users**

- **Tutors/Instructors**: register profiles, list districts, prices, availability; run classes and manage students.
- **Learners/Parents**: search by city→district, subject, schedule, price; request/enroll and read feedback.
- **Admins**: moderation, verification, catalog management.

**User environment & context**

- Web platform with fast, district-level discovery and booking; simple tools for classes and per-student feedback.
- Client is a web SPA for search, filters, profiles, booking UI (desktop/mobile browsers).

**Important mechanics to cover in the system (MVP)**

- **District catalog** (city→district; no map).
- **Availability slots** (weekly, recurring) and **filtering by availability**.
- **Search & Filter**: city, district, subject, price range, rating, availability; sorting/pagination.
- **Booking Requests**: request → accept/decline → status updates; simple inbox.
- **Classes/Groups & Rosters**; **Per-student feedback**.
- **Ratings & Reviews** (with moderation); **Admin tools** (verification, moderation, taxonomy).

**Main objectives of the project**

- **Time-to-match:** median time from search to first booking request < **10 minutes**.
- **Tutor utilization:** average classes ≥ **70%** of capacity by Week 8 pilot.
- **Quality/Performance:** P95 search latency < **1.2 s**; additional quality metrics.

**Goals to be satisfied & major features (brief)**

- **Auth & Roles** (Tutor/Learner/Admin), **Profiles**, **District catalog**, **Availability**, **Search & Filter**, **Booking**, **Classes**, **Feedback**, **Reviews**, **Admin console** (verification & moderation).

**Data we will gather and why**

- **User** (id, role, name, email, password hash) - identity/auth.
- **TutorProfile** (city, districts, bio, qualifications, price_hourly, rating_avg/count, subjects) - search & transparency.
- **AvailabilitySlot** - matching on free times.
- **Class** & **Enrollment** - group sessions and rosters.
- **Feedback** (per-student notes) - learning continuity (private to that student).
- **BookingRequest** - transaction flow and status.
- **Review** - quality signals for search.

## Project Deliverables

Deliverables include

- Project Proposal and Software Development Plan
- Requirements & User Stories; Wireframes → Clickable Prototype; DB Schema & API Spec; Deployed MVP (staging + prod) + basic Admin console.
- Architecture & ADRs; Test plan & cases; Accessibility checklist; Runbook (deploy, rollback, monitoring).
- Final demo, slides, short report.

## Assumptions and Constraints

**Assumptions**

- **District selection is adequate; no map/geolocation** in MVP.
- **No payment processing** (bookings arranged offline or via external means).
- **Web app expected**; standalone native apps not included.

**Constraints**

- **Performance** targets (search under 500 ms typical; P95 < 1.2 s), **Reliability** (99% weekly uptime pilot), **Security/Privacy** (hashed passwords; role-based access), **Accessibility** (WCAG 2.1 AA), **Maintainability** (module boundaries; tests), **Scalability** (4k users/1k profiles/20k searches per month).
- **Process & schedule:** Agile Scrum with 1-week sprints; 8-week plan with milestones (profiles, search & booking, classes/feedback, reviews/admin, hardening/demo).
- **Tools/Tech (reuse & interfaces):** React+TS (frontend), .NET or Spring Boot (backend), PostgreSQL + Redis, REST APIs; docs/PM in Notion/Google Docs; Figma for design.

**Overview (use, hardware, platform)**

- **Where used:** web (home/school/any browser); SPA client handles forms, filters, profiles, booking.
- **Target platform:** **Web SPA** (SaaS-style deployment). **No standalone apps** in MVP.

# Project Organization

## Development Process

**Model:** **Agile Scrum**, **1-week sprints**. Chosen because the UX and search relevance need iterative discovery and fast feedback; early increments de-risk profiles, search, and booking. Ceremonies: weekly planning, **daily 15-min standups**, sprint **demo**; **Definition of Done**: code reviewed, tests passed, accessibility labels, deployed to staging, docs updated.

**Team communication & tools:** Day-to-day coordination via sprint ceremonies above; working artifacts in **Notion/Google Docs** and **Figma**; source repo & CI/CD established in Week 1,

## Development Tools

- **Frontend:** React + TypeScript.
- **Backend:** C# (.NET) **or** Java (Spring Boot).
- **Database:** PostgreSQL (primary); **Redis** for caching sessions/search results.
- **Search:** PostgreSQL full-text with **GIN** indexes (MVP).
- **Docs & PM / Design:** **Notion**, **Google Docs**, **Figma**.
